    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concluded that the CFD hemolysis model provides sufficient evidence to support the COU2 regulatory submission. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was completed and NIH predictions fall below the clinical threshold at all assessed operating points. Credibility factor gaps were noted but judged acceptable given the conservative safety margins in the hemolysis threshold. The hemolysis scalar transport coefficients dataset (vintage 2018-03-15) was carried forward from the prior model build without re-validation against the January 2026 model revision; this was not flagged as a concern during the review cycle.",
